.Dd April 19, 2026
.Dt MPORT.INSTALL 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm mport.install
.Nd install one or more local mport package files
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl A
.Op Fl c Ar chroot-path
.Op Fl p Ar prefix
.Ar pkgfile ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
installs one or more local
.Pa .mport
package files using the low-level package installation path.
It is typically used as an internal helper by
.Xr mport 1 ,
but can also be invoked directly.
.Bl -tag -width ".Fl p Ar prefix"
.It Fl A
Mark installed packages as automatic dependencies.
.It Fl c Ar chroot-path
Run the installation inside the specified chroot.
.It Fl p Ar prefix
Override the installation prefix.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Install a local package file:
.Dl # mport.install hello-1.0.mport
.Pp
Install package files as automatic dependencies:
.Dl # mport.install -A dep1.mport dep2.mport
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr mport 1 ,
.Xr mport.create 1
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
utility appeared in
.Mx 0.3 .
